title._content: Group portrait of the NCPE Senior Gaelic Football team 1975/1976 (1)

description._content: Ref: C1/774 Back row left to right: Hugo Clerkin (Monaghan); Pat Spillane (Kerry); Jimmy Dunne (Offaly); Declan Smyth (Galway); Brian Talty (Galway); Liam Fardy (Wexford); Brian Murtagh (Westmeath); Tony Harkin (Donegal); Larry McCarthy (Cork). Middle row left to right: Martin Connolly (Mayo); Mick Caulfield (Wexford); Richie Bell – RIP (Mayo); Ted Owens (Cork); Mickey Houston (Donegal); Joe Mulligan (Offaly); Mike Spillane (Kerry) Front row left to right: Eddie Mahon (Wexford); Gerry Dillon (Kerry); Brian Mullins (Dublin- Captain; holding the Hodges Figgis Tropy); Fran Ryder (Dublin); Dick Dunne (Laois); Johnny O’ Connell (Kerry). Trophies: Ryan Cup – Higher Education Division One Football Trench Cup – Non-Universities Football Championship Sneem 7-a-side trophy Limerick City Football Championship Trophy. Brian Mullins is holding the Hodges Figgis trophy, a trophy presented by Hodges Figgis book publishers for competition between the Sigerson Cup winners and the Trench Cup winners.
